the main living room/dining room area.  The beach scenes in the slide show and maybe what you were thinking of is the common beach for all water point residents.  It is not owned by any one water point owner.\n \nAll bedrooms are under one roof.\n \nIt's in water point. Fully furnished; nothing needs to be done.  It's just too expensive.  Square footage is 5500 under roof in main home (does not include over garage apartment for live in help).  1200 square feet of patio.  Waterfront property.  Ownership of a buoy to which the owner attaches an included trampoline.  Includes Gym space, office space and media room.  Like I said, extravagant.  \n \nFor kicks, two weeks ago, I asked the broker to see if the owner would take 5 MM.  Owner .would not and would not make a counter claiming that we were simply too far apart.  According to the broker, the owner would not rent the place out either.\n \nI'll find out from broker what the house cost the owner, if the broker can get that info.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSee what's new at AOL.com and Make AOL Your Homepage.","body_html":"<html><head><style type=\"text/css\"><!-- DIV {margin:0px;} --></style></head><body><div style=\"font-family:times new roman, new york, times, serif;font-size:12pt\"><DIV style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman, new york, times, serif\">nope<BR><BR>\n<DIV style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman, new york, times, serif\">----- Original Message ----<BR>From: \"DKIESQ@aol.com\" &lt;DKIESQ@aol.com&gt;<BR>To: jeeproject@yahoo.com<BR>Sent: Thursday, October 25, 2007 8:56:53 PM<BR>Subject: Water Point<BR><BR><FONT id=role_document face=Arial color=#000000 size=2>\n<DIV>Attached is a slide show of the exterior of the big water point house and a few shots of the interior of the main living room/dining room area.&nbsp; The beach scenes in the slide show and maybe what you were thinking of is the common beach for all water point residents.&nbsp; It is not owned by any one water point owner.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>All bedrooms are under one roof.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>It's in water point.&nbsp;Fully furnished; nothing needs to be done.&nbsp; It's just too expensive.&nbsp; Square footage is 5500 under roof in main home (does not include over garage apartment for live in help).&nbsp; 1200 square feet of patio.&nbsp; Waterfront property.&nbsp; Ownership of a buoy to which the owner attaches an included trampoline.&nbsp; Includes Gym space, office space and media room.&nbsp; Like I said, extravagant.&nbsp; </DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>For kicks,&nbsp;two weeks ago,&nbsp;I asked the broker to see if the owner would take 5 MM.&nbsp; Owner .would not and would not make a counter claiming that we were simply too far apart.&nbsp; According to the broker, the owner would not rent the place out either.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>I'll find out from broker what the house cost the owner, if the broker can get that info.</DIV></FONT><BR><BR><BR>\n<DIV><FONT style=\"FONT: 10pt ARIAL,; COLOR: black\">\n<HR style=\"MARGIN-TOP: 10px\">\nSee what's new at <A title=http://www.aol.com?NCID=AOLCMP00300000001170 href=\"http://www.aol.com/?NCID=AOLCMP00300000001170\" target=_blank rel=nofollow>AOL.com</A> and <A title=http://www.aol.com/mksplash.adp?NCID=AOLCMP00300000001169 href=\"http://www.aol.com/mksplash.adp?NCID=AOLCMP00300000001169\" target=_blank rel=nofollow>Make AOL Your Homepage</A>.</FONT></DIV></DIV><BR></DIV></div></body></html>","is_from_epstein":true,"attachments":0,"avatar_color":"#9c27b0","stars":1,"is_redacted":false}]